720194f-a.text:
Greenwich Street, north from Cortlandt Street, showing surface conditions under the Ninth Avenue Elevated. Note that the street car tracks are being removed. The intersection in the midground is Dey Street.
June 2, 1937
W. P. A. photo
Five Boroughs Project

720192f-b.text:
Greenwich Street, north from Cortlandt Street, as photographed from the downtown "E1" platform showing details of the station here prior to demolition. In the center is an express platform and across same is an enclosed passageway connecting the various units. The white building in the background is the new U. S. Fereral Office
Building and Post Office.
June 7, 1940
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr
